I feel terrible.

249
00:11:33.973 --> 00:11:36.065
Oh. no. Don't be silly.

250
00:11:36.158 --> 00:11:39.080
If you could give me a call
the next time you see him.

251
00:11:39.171 --> 00:11:40.920
I would be ever so grateful.

252
00:11:41.042 --> 00:11:42.323
"Bill Houston."

253
00:11:42.411 --> 00:11:43.745
Y-you're
a private investigator?

254
00:11:43.856 --> 00:11:45.220
He in some kind of trouble.

255
00:11:45.321 --> 00:11:47.081
According to the missus.
always.

256
00:11:47.165 --> 00:11:48.258
Gambling.

257
00:11:48.335 --> 00:11:49.915
He lost his daughter's
college fund

258
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:52.898
playing Caribbean Stud.
left home in embarrassment.

259
00:11:53.007 --> 00:11:54.900
Helen's worried sick.
It's a mess.

260
00:11:55.065 --> 00:11:57.139
You said he was moving?

261
00:11:57.231 --> 00:11:59.470
People here don't stay long.

262
00:11:59.558 --> 00:12:01.471
I mean. I saw him
with a truck in the alley.

263
00:12:01.555 --> 00:12:02.704
What kind of truck?

264
00:12:03.061 --> 00:12:04.411
Reddington
didn't give it to me.

265
00:12:04.508 --> 00:12:06.835
I found it
in one of the places he stays.

266
00:12:06.972 --> 00:12:08.597
And you think this is a photo
of your mother?

267
00:12:08.690 --> 00:12:10.256
I don't know.
That's what Reddington told me.

268
00:12:10.342 --> 00:12:12.108
But that girl.
that is definitely me.

269
00:12:12.254 --> 00:12:14.160
The agent back there.
the CI he mentioned?

270
00:12:14.307 --> 00:12:15.664
That could be my chance
to find out something

271
00:12:15.745 --> 00:12:17.592
about the woman holding me
in that photo.

272
00:12:18.386 --> 00:12:19.624
Why would a Russian CI

273
00:12:19.731 --> 00:12:21.235
have information
about your mother?

274
00:12:25.917 --> 00:12:26.959
Ressler.

275
00:12:27.054 --> 00:12:28.907
- Where are you?
- Just leaving the Orea. Why?

276
00:12:29.014 --> 00:12:29.775
Reddington called.

277
00:12:29.880 --> 00:12:32.092
Karakurt is in possession
of an ANFO IED.

278
00:12:32.199 --> 00:12:34.295
We've identified the vehicle.
It's a white moving truck

279
00:12:34.387 --> 00:12:39.058
rented out of Annapolis.
plate number Delta-Kilo-5-8-2-7.

280
00:12:39.176 --> 00:12:40.937
We're trying to ping
the location now.

281
00:12:41.042 --> 00:12:42.782
They think Karakurt
has a white moving truck

282
00:12:42.870 --> 00:12:44.656
with explosives.

283
00:12:49.280 --> 00:12:50.250
Oh. my God.

284
00:12:50.336 --> 00:12:52.184
The truck is parked
right outside of Orea

285
00:12:52.292 --> 00:12:54.143
Orea is the target.

286
00:12:54.261 --> 00:12:55.828
Liz! Liz. look out!
The truck!

287
00:13:20.701 --> 00:13:23.308
<i>Crews continue the grim work</i>
<i>of sifting through the rubble.</i>

288
00:13:23.414 --> 00:13:25.334
<i>The death toll stands at 14.</i>
<i>although the identities...</i>

289
00:13:25.439 --> 00:13:26.981
<i>This was an act</i>
<i>of terror. plain and simple.</i>

290
00:13:27.098 --> 00:13:29.295
<i>As Chairman of the Select</i>
<i>Committee on Intelligence.</i>

291
00:13:29.393 --> 00:13:30.404
<i>mark my words.</i>

292
00:13:30.500 --> 00:13:32.605
<i>We will find the people</i>
<i>who are responsible.</i>

293
00:13:32.725 --> 00:13:33.297
<i>And when we do. we will respond</i>
<i>with all appropriate force.</i>

294
00:13:33.427 --> 00:13:35.705
It's official.
No survivors.

295
00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:36.728
I got something.

296
00:13:36.837 --> 00:13:40.242
Security cam from a loading dock
on 20th and Independence.

297
00:13:41.087 --> 00:13:43.441
It's not much.
but let's send it wide.

298
00:13:43.539 --> 00:13:45.893
see if we can't get lucky.
get an ID.

299
00:13:49.853 --> 00:13:51.332
- Keen.
- You're okay.

300
00:13:51.434 --> 00:13:53.389
I was afraid
you were... inside.

301
00:13:53.485 --> 00:13:57.500
No. but those agents--
their entire section.

302
00:13:57.624 --> 00:13:59.434
Every agent on that desk
was wiped out.

303
00:13:59.550 --> 00:14:02.337
- If this gets traced back to Russia--
- Not "If." Lizzy.

304
00:14:02.439 --> 00:14:03.943
Senator Hawkins
has taken the bait

305
00:14:04.047 --> 00:14:05.743
like a bluegill to a cricket.

306
00:14:05.838 --> 00:14:08.763
And where he goes. the
warmongers are sure to follow.

307
00:14:08.862 --> 00:14:10.164
Where are you on Karakurt?

308
00:14:10.256 --> 00:14:11.933
Where? Nowhere.

309
00:14:12.087 --> 00:14:13.520
The Cabal just took out

310
00:14:13.617 --> 00:14:16.180
an entire substation
of the CIA.

311
00:14:16.525 --> 00:14:18.673
They put a bullet in your chest.
and you have no idea how.

312
00:14:18.757 --> 00:14:20.458
You're the most
cautious person I know.

313
00:14:20.540 --> 00:14:22.045
The FBI couldn't find you
for 20 years.

314
00:14:22.140 --> 00:14:23.768
but they did.

315
00:14:23.930 --> 00:14:24.905
They're three steps ahead.

316
00:14:24.987 --> 00:14:27.464
and that's exactly
what I'm gonna tell the AG.

317
00:14:27.545 --> 00:14:29.209
Tom Connolly is there?

318
00:14:29.298 --> 00:14:31.030
No. he's on his way.

319
00:14:31.391 --> 00:14:33.967
I assume he's expecting
to be briefed.

320
00:14:34.860 --> 00:14:37.675
Connolly made the Harbormaster
investigation go away.

321
00:14:37.765 --> 00:14:40.366
All we have on Karakurt
is a recording

322
00:14:40.482 --> 00:14:42.598
and a grainy photo
that's gotten us nowhere.

323
00:14:42.706 --> 00:14:44.661
- You have far more than that.
- Like what?

324
00:14:44.768 --> 00:14:47.628
I'm glad you're safe. Lizzy.
I'll be in touch.

325
00:14:51.494 --> 00:14:54.399
_

326
00:14:54.627 --> 00:14:56.008
_

327
00:14:56.162 --> 00:14:59.101
_

328
00:14:59.228 --> 00:15:01.372
_

329
00:15:13.333 --> 00:15:14.612
Mr. Houston?

330
00:15:15.024 --> 00:15:17.784
The man with the truck.
he's back.

331
00:15:19.470 --> 00:15:21.659
Reddington has a location
for Karakurt--

332
00:15:21.800 --> 00:15:23.423
63rd and Franklin.

333
00:15:23.522 --> 00:15:26.322
Coordinate with HRT.
Roll out now.

334
00:15:30.489 --> 00:15:31.712
We have a lead.

335
00:15:32.644 --> 00:15:35.782
We need to talk in your office.

336
00:15:40.269 --> 00:15:40.952
Tom.

337
00:15:41.078 --> 00:15:42.547
You will ignore
Reddington's lead.

338
00:15:42.685 --> 00:15:43.773
Why?
I'm sure it's solid.

339
00:15:43.873 --> 00:15:45.270
Harold. call your team.

340
00:15:45.412 --> 00:15:48.754
Tell them intel indicates
the Russian is at Union Station.

341
00:15:48.848 --> 00:15:50.127
You expect me
to let Karakurt get away?

342
00:15:50.213 --> 00:15:51.690
The man murdered
14 government agents.

343
00:15:51.777 --> 00:15:52.813
And that is a national tragedy.

344
00:15:52.908 --> 00:15:54.408
but finding him
will not bring them back.

345
00:15:54.496 --> 00:15:55.850
What about his next target?

346
00:15:56.129 --> 00:15:57.161
How many more lives
does he have to take

347
00:15:57.258 --> 00:15:58.608
before you let me do my job?

348
00:15:58.691 --> 00:16:01.479
Your job today is to divert
your team to Union Station.

349
00:16:01.567 --> 00:16:06.165
or. God forbid.
your wife will pay the price.

350
00:16:07.678 --> 00:16:09.670
Charlene is a lovely woman

351
00:16:10.412 --> 00:16:12.721
who violated
the Espionage Act...

352
00:16:12.823 --> 00:16:14.376
for you.

353
00:16:14.521 --> 00:16:16.606
Prison will not be kind to her.

354
00:16:16.701 --> 00:16:20.789
Harold. let him go.
This is bigger than both of us.

355
00:16:25.027 --> 00:16:26.409
Ressler.

356
00:16:26.515 --> 00:16:27.603
We received actionable intel

357
00:16:27.692 --> 00:16:29.031
that conflicts
with Reddington's.

358
00:16:29.118 --> 00:16:30.888
Yeah. but Keen said
that he had an eyewitness.

359
00:16:30.978 --> 00:16:32.557
Local PD got a hit
off the credit card

360
00:16:32.680 --> 00:16:34.799
Karakurt used
to rent the truck.

361
00:16:34.940 --> 00:16:37.809
Same card was used to purchase
a train ticket at Union Station.

362
00:16:37.906 --> 00:16:40.854
- Redirect there now.
- Copy that.

363
00:16:45.047 --> 00:16:47.165
I knew you'd make
the right play.

364
00:16:47.723 --> 00:16:49.483
Give Charlene my regards.

365
00:16:57.752 --> 00:16:59.914
_

366
00:17:11.762 --> 00:17:13.158
Check the platforms.

367
00:17:50.325 --> 00:17:52.461
I've got eyes.
Going through Gate D.

368
00:17:58.665 --> 00:18:00.374
Keen. what's your 20?

369
00:18:05.150 --> 00:18:06.713
Hey. hang on.
You okay?

370
00:18:06.846 --> 00:18:08.523
- Yeah. I'm okay.
- What happened?

371
00:18:08.693 --> 00:18:10.090
He blind-sided me.

372
00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:11.832
Okay.
Where did he go?

373
00:18:12.388 --> 00:18:13.900
I didn't see.

374
00:18:17.533 --> 00:18:19.767
<i>The Intelligence Committee</i>
<i>is receiving live updates</i>

375
00:18:19.875 --> 00:18:21.434
<i>on the progress</i>
<i>of the investigation</i>

376
00:18:21.540 --> 00:18:22.939
<i>from the Justice Department.</i>

377
00:18:23.041 --> 00:18:24.817
<i>All evidence</i>
<i>points to a deliberate.</i>

378
00:18:24.922 --> 00:18:26.625
<i>sanctioned attack</i>
<i>from Russia's SVR.</i>

379
00:18:26.714 --> 00:18:27.370
It was Karakurt.

380
00:18:27.459 --> 00:18:28.578
He was there.
You're certain?

381
00:18:28.658 --> 00:18:29.942
I don't know.
He came around the corner.

382
00:18:30.033 --> 00:18:31.300
I-I just
got a glimpse of him.

383
00:18:31.376 --> 00:18:33.642
I was calling Ressler for backup
when he knocked me down.

384
00:18:33.723 --> 00:18:35.127
Hey. guys.
Listen to this.

385
00:18:35.363 --> 00:18:37.729
From the recording
Agent Masik gave you.

386
00:18:38.506 --> 00:18:39.526
<i>Tell me it worked.</i>

387
00:18:39.610 --> 00:18:42.182
<i>The proof of concept</i>
<i>succeeded as projected.</i>

388
00:18:42.281 --> 00:18:44.316
<i>- Prepare to initiate Phase Two.</i>
<i>- Done.</i>

389
00:18:44.404 --> 00:18:45.422
<i>I've identified the markers</i>

390
00:18:45.513 --> 00:18:47.399
<i>for targeting</i>
<i>and customization.</i>

391
00:18:47.489 --> 00:18:48.981
Whatever's happening.
it is happening soon.

392
00:18:49.071 --> 00:18:50.522
What does he mean by "Markers"?

393
00:18:50.613 --> 00:18:51.760
Could be referencing
map coordinates.

394
00:18:51.850 --> 00:18:53.777
some kind of radio beacon.
We don't know.

395
00:18:53.856 --> 00:18:55.173
But based on
what Agent Masik told you.

396
00:18:55.274 --> 00:18:56.977
we think we've figured out
who the CI is.

397
00:18:57.062 --> 00:18:59.704
He told you that the owner
runs a restaurant in DC

398
00:18:59.780 --> 00:19:01.356
that caters
to the Soviet Old Guard.

399
00:19:01.456 --> 00:19:02.515
We reviewed ownership records

400
00:19:02.612 --> 00:19:05.346
for all the Russian restaurants
in DC and found one.

401
00:19:05.445 --> 00:19:07.690
Ninoshka's.
The owner is former Spetsnaz.

402
00:19:07.778 --> 00:19:10.596
His name is Anton Velov.
My belief is he's the CI.

403
00:19:10.697 --> 00:19:12.079
The conversation
was recorded last night.

404
00:19:12.194 --> 00:19:13.092
so we pulled all the receipts

405
00:19:13.195 --> 00:19:15.048
and found a late dinner for two

406
00:19:15.205 --> 00:19:18.262
paid for by a Leo Andropov.

407
00:19:18.356 --> 00:19:19.570
<i>Dr.</i> Leo Andropov.

408
00:19:19.676 --> 00:19:21.237
And you think
he was meeting with Karakurt?

409
00:19:21.354 --> 00:19:24.285
I'd say yes. Andropov worked
for the Soviet Defense Ministry

410
00:19:24.388 --> 00:19:26.420
in the final months
before Glasnost.

411
00:19:26.551 --> 00:19:28.137
Whiz kid.

412
00:19:28.229 --> 00:19:30.850
When he was 16. he published
his first and last paper

413
00:19:30.948 --> 00:19:32.890
in an open-source
microbiology journal

414
00:19:33.052 --> 00:19:36.016
before he got snapped up
by the Weapons Ministry.

415
00:19:36.528 --> 00:19:37.386
Closet's clear!

416
00:19:37.467 --> 00:19:39.768
I've seen equipment like this
at the lab at Quantico.

417
00:19:39.879 --> 00:19:41.236
This is a genotyping unit.

418
00:19:41.431 --> 00:19:43.555
It looks like Andropov fled.

419
00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:46.001
No passport. no ID.
no prescription drugs.

420
00:19:46.091 --> 00:19:48.842
Building fertilizer bombs is
way below this guy's pay grade.

421
00:19:48.950 --> 00:19:50.381
This can't be
Karakurt's endgame.

422
00:19:50.562 --> 00:19:53.787
- Biological weapons?
- This guy's a virologist.

423
00:19:53.880 --> 00:19:55.100
If these
are biological weapons.

424
00:19:55.187 --> 00:19:57.431
then we may be looking
at a pandemic.

425
00:20:00.481 --> 00:20:02.729
It always starts with a favor.

426
00:20:02.812 --> 00:20:05.073
I've known Tom Connolly
for two decades.

427
00:20:05.152 --> 00:20:06.847
He's had dinners at my house.

428
00:20:06.933 --> 00:20:09.159
And when he offered to help me
get into that drug trial.

429
00:20:09.319 --> 00:20:11.001
it was my only hope.

430
00:20:11.081 --> 00:20:12.820
It wasn't just<i> your</i> hope.
Harold.

431
00:20:12.909 --> 00:20:14.959
It was your wife's hope.
you children's.

432
00:20:15.052 --> 00:20:17.875
You were given
a terminal diagnosis.

433
00:20:18.044 --> 00:20:20.296
and Connolly ends up
offering you a choice--

434
00:20:20.380 --> 00:20:23.049
your life or your ethics.
and you picked your life.

435
00:20:23.136 --> 00:20:24.028
What good are ethics

436
00:20:24.127 --> 00:20:26.209
if you aren't alive
to live by them?

437
00:20:26.292 --> 00:20:28.891
If it was just me.
my health. my life.

438
00:20:28.984 --> 00:20:31.838
I would have told him
to pound sand a long time ago.

439
00:20:31.970 --> 00:20:34.075
When he dragged
Charlene into it-- now this--

440
00:20:34.179 --> 00:20:36.154
deliberately misdirecting
my own agents

441
00:20:36.299 --> 00:20:38.297
to facilitate
the escape of a terrorist!

442
00:20:38.379 --> 00:20:39.859
Now. that's what's interesting.

443
00:20:39.941 --> 00:20:42.249
He orders you
to send them to Union Station.

444
00:20:42.352 --> 00:20:45.260
ostensibly to throw them
off Karakurt's trail.

445
00:20:45.360 --> 00:20:46.858
And there he is.

446
00:20:47.883 --> 00:20:50.241
Perhaps Agent Keen
was mistaken.

447
00:20:50.332 --> 00:20:52.277
And assaulted
by a total stranger?

448
00:20:52.745 --> 00:20:54.142
That makes even less sense.

449
00:20:54.229 --> 00:20:56.209
It was some kind of ambush.

450
00:20:56.428 --> 00:20:58.371
And I sent my people
right into it.

451
00:20:59.005 --> 00:21:00.863
And a good thing you did.

452
00:21:00.967 --> 00:21:01.917
What the hell does that mean?

453
00:21:02.006 --> 00:21:04.719
Thanks to your desire
to protect Charlene.

454
00:21:04.810 --> 00:21:06.889
we're presented
with a unique opportunity

455
00:21:06.981 --> 00:21:08.693
to find out
what the Cabal is up to.

456
00:21:08.778 --> 00:21:09.999
How?

457
00:21:10.145 --> 00:21:12.229
By continuing
to follow Connolly's orders

458
00:21:12.320 --> 00:21:13.728
without question.

459
00:21:13.818 --> 00:21:16.662
The last thing you should do
is confront him.

460
00:21:16.843 --> 00:21:19.195
Gather evidence.
Build a case.

461
00:21:19.282 --> 00:21:22.318
Tom Connolly's been leaking
information to the Cabal

462
00:21:22.412 --> 00:21:24.562
about everything
that goes on in this place

463
00:21:24.691 --> 00:21:26.794
ever since he walked
through that door

464
00:21:26.903 --> 00:21:29.550
and offered to save your life.

465
00:21:29.679 --> 00:21:31.872
You want to wipe
that debt clean?

466
00:21:31.956 --> 00:21:34.482
Keep your eyes open
and your mouth shut.

467
00:21:35.620 --> 00:21:37.900
We found
a fully outfitted virology lab

468
00:21:38.001 --> 00:21:39.158
in Andropov's apartment.

469
00:21:39.287 --> 00:21:41.009
Think he's building
a bio-weapon.

470
00:21:41.096 --> 00:21:42.100
We seized his notebooks.

471
00:21:42.184 --> 00:21:44.484
but we're gonna need
an expert in microbiology

472
00:21:44.574 --> 00:21:46.698
who can also translate Russian.

473
00:21:55.382 --> 00:21:56.662
Reddy Bear!

474
00:21:56.748 --> 00:21:58.298
Oh. I could eat you alive!

475
00:21:58.401 --> 00:22:00.473
- Mm.
- Mwah.

476
00:22:00.681 --> 00:22:03.518
Ginger. this is
Dr. Lauren Kimberly.

477
00:22:03.625 --> 00:22:08.133
Lauren. my executive assistant.
Ginger Lumiere.

478
00:22:08.280 --> 00:22:10.090
Hmm.
Interesting look.

479
00:22:10.267 --> 00:22:12.435
Purposeful. but still feminine.

480
00:22:12.582 --> 00:22:14.351
You should try
a darker shade of lipstick.

481
00:22:14.449 --> 00:22:16.700
I bet you could
get away with a gloss.

482
00:22:16.806 --> 00:22:19.953
Lauren. we're going to have to
forgo the makeover today.

483
00:22:20.049 --> 00:22:21.563
We're in a bit of a pinch.

484
00:22:21.661 --> 00:22:24.588
Understood.
Let me see what I can do.

485
00:22:28.771 --> 00:22:30.625
I've got a lead on my mom.

486
00:22:31.017 --> 00:22:33.302
An Orea agent. he has a CI

487
00:22:33.405 --> 00:22:35.439
who might know something
about Katarina Rostova.

488
00:22:35.539 --> 00:22:37.779
Dr. Kimberly
was a tenured professor

489
00:22:37.883 --> 00:22:40.280
doing genome research
at Stanford

490
00:22:40.367 --> 00:22:42.945
when she was recruited
by the private sector.

491
00:22:43.124 --> 00:22:44.800
I'm gonna find out the truth.

492
00:22:44.907 --> 00:22:46.874
She makes her real money
consulting.

493
00:22:46.965 --> 00:22:48.307
Costs a fortune.

494
00:22:48.387 --> 00:22:50.911
She did. however.
let me name a lipstick color--

495
00:22:51.005 --> 00:22:53.214
"Fire In The Hole."

496
00:22:55.579 --> 00:22:56.690
_

497
00:22:58.973 --> 00:23:00.436
<i>You've reached Elizabeth Keen.</i>

498
00:23:00.540 --> 00:23:02.187
<i>Please leave your message</i>
<i>at the tone.</i>

499
00:23:02.431 --> 00:23:05.257
Hi. Liz.
This is. uh. Jacob.

500
00:23:05.418 --> 00:23:06.963
Jacob Phelps.

501
00:23:07.054 --> 00:23:08.183
Look. I know
things are complicated.

502
00:23:08.271 --> 00:23:10.250
I know you're
going through a bad breakup.

503
00:23:10.657 --> 00:23:12.681
But from what I heard.
the guy's a total loser.

504
00:23:12.771 --> 00:23:14.958
Couldn't cook.
made crappy pancakes.

505
00:23:15.046 --> 00:23:19.917
So I wanted to see if you would
join me for dinner tomorrow.

506
00:23:20.002 --> 00:23:22.567
Uh. I made a reservation at 7:00
at this great little place

507
00:23:22.668 --> 00:23:26.453
on the corner of 32nd and M.
and I hope that you will come.

508
00:23:28.119 --> 00:23:29.170
Or not.

509
00:23:29.308 --> 00:23:31.979
But. uh. either way.
I'll be there.

510
00:23:35.329 --> 00:23:37.416
You're right.
It is a weapon.

511
00:23:37.567 --> 00:23:38.409
A WMD?

512
00:23:38.505 --> 00:23:40.622
No. A<i> WID--</i>

513
00:23:40.721 --> 00:23:42.753
a weapon of
individual destruction.

514
00:23:42.897 --> 00:23:44.457
This is a customized virus.

515
00:23:44.543 --> 00:23:46.016
synthesized
with the sole intent

516
00:23:46.128 --> 00:23:48.113
of killing
one specific individual.

517
00:23:48.227 --> 00:23:49.524
How is that possible?

518
00:23:49.616 --> 00:23:52.015
He's created
a supercharged rotavirus.

519
00:23:52.159 --> 00:23:53.205
These are very common.

520
00:23:53.299 --> 00:23:55.880
By the age of 5. most of us have
been infected multiple times.

521
00:23:55.973 --> 00:23:58.267
And with each infection.
we build up an immunity.

522
00:23:58.361 --> 00:24:00.093
So it's harmless
to most people.

523
00:24:00.214 --> 00:24:02.417
<i>All</i> people. Precisely.

524
00:24:02.535 --> 00:24:04.615
But this rotavirus
has been customized.

525
00:24:04.710 --> 00:24:06.264
keyed to infect one individual

526
00:24:06.369 --> 00:24:09.800
with a unique genetic sequence.
and to devastating effect.

527
00:24:09.888 --> 00:24:12.115
According to the animal trials
logged in these notes.

528
00:24:12.232 --> 00:24:13.963
it attacks
the central nervous system

529
00:24:14.060 --> 00:24:15.718
within minutes of exposure.

530
00:24:15.809 --> 00:24:17.126
One person.

531
00:24:17.215 --> 00:24:18.042
But who?

532
00:24:18.132 --> 00:24:19.836
I can only tell you
what they're doing.

533
00:24:20.096 --> 00:24:25.594
I'm sorry. but I can't tell you
<i>who</i> they're doing it to.

534
00:24:36.691 --> 00:24:38.955
So. we know Karakurt
is targeting one person

535
00:24:39.082 --> 00:24:41.207
and it's keyed
to his or her DNA.

536
00:24:41.302 --> 00:24:42.996
Think.

537
00:24:43.169 --> 00:24:45.065
He bombed the CIA's
Russian section.

538
00:24:45.151 --> 00:24:48.145
That took time. money
and no small amount of risk.

539
00:24:48.246 --> 00:24:50.461
What happens when
the United States is attacked.

540
00:24:50.552 --> 00:24:52.525
suffers grievous loss of life?

541
00:24:52.612 --> 00:24:54.409
We go into lock-down.

542
00:24:55.145 --> 00:24:58.194
The bombing bumped
the NTAS level to red.

543
00:24:58.353 --> 00:24:59.410
But why put the mission at risk

544
00:24:59.580 --> 00:25:01.823
by triggering
a high-level terrorist alert?

545
00:25:01.914 --> 00:25:03.006
Well. that's the downside.

546
00:25:03.097 --> 00:25:06.079
The upside is exposure.
public attention.

547
00:25:06.174 --> 00:25:07.404
Remember.
the people behind this

548
00:25:07.491 --> 00:25:09.696
went to immense trouble
and expense.

549
00:25:09.808 --> 00:25:11.477
What does that say
about their target?

550
00:25:11.567 --> 00:25:13.300
He's high-value.

551
00:25:15.655 --> 00:25:17.801
Someone important.

552
00:25:20.676 --> 00:25:22.360
Oh. my God.
that's why he did it.

553
00:25:22.441 --> 00:25:24.014
The Memorial Service.

554
00:25:24.126 --> 00:25:26.580
The victims will be
memorialized at a service

555
00:25:26.721 --> 00:25:29.307
at Ascension
and Saint Agnes Church.

556
00:25:29.406 --> 00:25:31.368
Politicians and
military personnel.

557
00:25:31.464 --> 00:25:33.433
intelligence officers
from overseas

558
00:25:33.530 --> 00:25:35.672
will all be there
to pay their respects.

559
00:25:35.760 --> 00:25:38.229
One of them is the target.

560
00:25:43.777 --> 00:25:45.017
So. this is the guy?

561
00:25:45.114 --> 00:25:46.372
That's the best we can do.

562
00:25:46.480 --> 00:25:48.106
He's our prime suspect
in the Orea bombing.

563
00:25:48.199 --> 00:25:50.142
and we have good reason to
believe that he's not done yet.

564
00:25:50.224 --> 00:25:51.558
We need your people
to be on high alert.

565
00:25:51.650 --> 00:25:52.720
We're looking for a bomb?

566
00:25:52.807 --> 00:25:54.682
No. we'll be prepared
for that possibility.

567
00:25:54.787 --> 00:25:57.235
but our intel says
he's after a specific target.

568
00:25:57.324 --> 00:25:58.456
We just don't know who yet.

569
00:25:58.542 --> 00:26:00.067
We'll do our best. but with
this many people around.

570
00:26:00.155 --> 00:26:01.404
I can't promise anything.

571
00:26:01.504 --> 00:26:03.038
Safest play
is to cancel the event.

572
00:26:03.158 --> 00:26:04.826
Believe me.
we're working on it.

573
00:26:05.511 --> 00:26:06.725
Just spoke to Reven Wright.

574
00:26:06.821 --> 00:26:08.829
Calling off the memorial service
is a nonstarter.

575
00:26:08.904 --> 00:26:11.195
That's a mistake. We have hard
evidence of a clear threat.

576
00:26:11.300 --> 00:26:12.758
Main Justice is aware.

577
00:26:12.886 --> 00:26:14.302
But the public's rattled
by this bombing.

578
00:26:14.390 --> 00:26:15.519
and they want
a show of strength.

579
00:26:15.621 --> 00:26:17.067
If they cancel.
it suggests we can't

580
00:26:17.167 --> 00:26:18.796
protect our own people
on our own turf.

581
00:26:18.868 --> 00:26:20.857
Maybe we can't-- at this point.
we still don't know

582
00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:22.155
exactly what
we're dealing with.

583
00:26:22.242 --> 00:26:24.673
I can tell you what I'm dealing
with-- an impossible problem.

584
00:26:24.762 --> 00:26:27.407
So if you're counting on me
cracking this virus. don't.

585
00:26:27.490 --> 00:26:28.713
Well. what<i> do</i> you have?

586
00:26:28.807 --> 00:26:29.695
We found the formula
for the virus

587
00:26:29.792 --> 00:26:30.842
in Karakurt's apartment.

588
00:26:30.944 --> 00:26:33.572
So my plan was
to reverse engineer the process.

589
00:26:33.661 --> 00:26:35.846
We are trying
millions of DNA combinations.

590
00:26:35.975 --> 00:26:38.176
If I could figure out the profile
it was engineered to destroy--

591
00:26:38.278 --> 00:26:40.328
You could run the profile
through the DNA database.

592
00:26:40.462 --> 00:26:42.089
If you get a match.
that's Karakurt's target.

593
00:26:42.185 --> 00:26:44.178
Except it won't work--
not in time. at least.

594
00:26:44.277 --> 00:26:46.670
I need hours--
days. maybe--

595
00:26:46.782 --> 00:26:48.336
and the memorial will be over

596
00:26:48.424 --> 00:26:50.374
long before we can ID
the target sequence.

597
00:26:50.472 --> 00:26:51.637
Whatever his plan.
we have to assume

598
00:26:51.733 --> 00:26:53.628
Karakurt's already infected
himself with the contagion

599
00:26:53.722 --> 00:26:55.473
and is a live carrier.

600
00:26:56.927 --> 00:26:58.965
Civilian and military
security assets

601
00:26:59.070 --> 00:27:00.313
have been marshalled
for the service.

602
00:27:00.394 --> 00:27:02.086
However. the assassin
in this case

603
00:27:02.188 --> 00:27:03.210
is not armed with something

604
00:27:03.312 --> 00:27:05.229
that we can flag
with a metal detector.

605
00:27:06.062 --> 00:27:08.292
The virus is transmitted
through touch.

606
00:27:08.469 --> 00:27:10.278
It penetrates the skin.

607
00:27:10.385 --> 00:27:11.822
Even brushing up
against the target

608
00:27:11.934 --> 00:27:14.104
is enough
to infect and kill him.

609
00:27:14.339 --> 00:27:16.598
It is critical
that we nail Karakurt

610
00:27:16.696 --> 00:27:18.697
before he can get
anywhere near that church.

611
00:27:18.806 --> 00:27:21.529
Find him. people!
Whatever it takes!

612
00:27:21.624 --> 00:27:23.751
- What are you thinking?
- Not me. Leonard.

613
00:27:23.891 --> 00:27:26.985
The Director.
What is<i> he</i> thinking?

614
00:27:27.096 --> 00:27:30.967
His objective is to exacerbate
tensions with Russia.

615
00:27:31.069 --> 00:27:32.812
He chose to send Karakurt.

616
00:27:32.922 --> 00:27:35.298
an assassin
known to work for the regime

617
00:27:35.445 --> 00:27:38.282
so people will assume
Russia is responsible.

618
00:27:38.373 --> 00:27:40.000
So...

619
00:27:40.156 --> 00:27:44.217
So whoever he's targeting next
will be an enemy of Russia.

620
00:27:44.331 --> 00:27:46.195
an outspoken critic.

621
00:27:46.284 --> 00:27:47.635
Someone people will believe

622
00:27:47.717 --> 00:27:49.965
the Russians
would want to silence.

623
00:28:02.682 --> 00:28:05.170
Hey. Keen! Keen!

624
00:28:05.282 --> 00:28:07.583
67 guests
have been cleared to attend.

625
00:28:08.127 --> 00:28:09.768
There's Defense. Homeland.

626
00:28:09.889 --> 00:28:12.476
CIA. the Bureau on this list.

627
00:28:13.220 --> 00:28:14.573
It's gonna be hard
to narrow it down.

628
00:28:14.656 --> 00:28:16.157
Yeah. so much
for the good old days

629
00:28:16.244 --> 00:28:17.723
where you could just
look for the glint

630
00:28:17.814 --> 00:28:20.193
of a sniper-rifle scope
in a nearby window.

631
00:28:20.281 --> 00:28:22.829
What does it do.
this virus. to the body?

632
00:28:22.919 --> 00:28:24.949
The CDC's
still breaking it down.

633
00:28:25.084 --> 00:28:27.638
But they're saying it attacks
the central nervous system.

634
00:28:27.743 --> 00:28:31.154
A victim would start shaking
within seconds of infection.

635
00:28:31.253 --> 00:28:34.835
Disorientation. then labored
breathing. convulsions.

636
00:28:34.922 --> 00:28:38.790
Incapacitation
within moments of contact.

637
00:28:38.922 --> 00:28:41.338
It's quite a remarkable feat
of engineering.

638
00:28:41.427 --> 00:28:44.376
In my experience.
such accomplishments

639
00:28:44.476 --> 00:28:45.920
don't happen overnight.

640
00:28:46.015 --> 00:28:47.850
You're saying
they tested it first.

641
00:28:47.940 --> 00:28:49.407
A customized virus

642
00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:53.254
deadly to such a small fraction
of the population--

643
00:28:53.932 --> 00:28:57.293
What kind of trial and error
would prove useful?

644
00:28:57.589 --> 00:28:59.077
This is Aram.

645
00:28:59.178 --> 00:29:01.649
Agent Mojtabai.
I need a list of people

646
00:29:01.738 --> 00:29:04.545
admitted to an Emergency Room
in the last few days

647
00:29:04.647 --> 00:29:05.581
displaying symptoms

648
00:29:05.684 --> 00:29:07.975
consistent with the virus
you're tracking.

649
00:29:08.077 --> 00:29:10.274
Okay. that's not gonna be
so easy to put together.

650
00:29:10.350 --> 00:29:12.857
Aram. that kind of
catastrophic trauma

651
00:29:12.945 --> 00:29:15.109
would certainly
have gotten someone's attention.

652
00:29:15.202 --> 00:29:16.978
It's on an autopsy chart
somewhere.

653
00:29:17.105 --> 00:29:19.074
Okay. I hear you.
but you have to--

654
00:29:19.954 --> 00:29:20.941
Whoa.

655
00:29:21.267 --> 00:29:22.378
Whoa.

656
00:29:22.481 --> 00:29:23.600
Bethesda General
sent tissue samples

657
00:29:23.707 --> 00:29:25.731
to the CDC a few days ago.

658
00:29:25.822 --> 00:29:28.806
A suspicious death
of a college student.

659
00:29:28.892 --> 00:29:30.541
The Center's just starting
an investigation.

660
00:29:30.639 --> 00:29:31.998
I need that student's
home address.

661
00:29:32.107 --> 00:29:34.568
and I need to speak
to Agent Navabi.

662
00:29:35.095 --> 00:29:38.065
Mrs. Jennings.
thank you for seeing me.

663
00:29:38.164 --> 00:29:40.381
I know this is
an extremely difficult time.

664
00:29:40.475 --> 00:29:43.702
I got a message from the CDC
about the investigation.

665
00:29:44.012 --> 00:29:46.877
But I didn't think they'd be
sending someone over so quickly.

666
00:29:46.971 --> 00:29:49.606
Can you tell me about Connor?
What you know so far?

667
00:29:49.692 --> 00:29:51.618
Not much.

668
00:29:51.797 --> 00:29:53.773
Connor was a law student.

669
00:29:53.864 --> 00:29:56.137
I was told he was walking
across campus

670
00:29:56.256 --> 00:30:00.644
when he just started shaking.
and then convulsing.

671
00:30:01.373 --> 00:30:02.950
One of the doctors suggested

672
00:30:03.034 --> 00:30:06.090
he may have contracted
a rare form of rotavirus?

673
00:30:06.175 --> 00:30:07.481
No. you're right to be thinking

674
00:30:07.575 --> 00:30:09.710
this could be
something else entirely.

675
00:30:09.791 --> 00:30:12.201
- Perhaps malicious.
- Malicious?

676
00:30:12.281 --> 00:30:13.438
To be honest.
Mrs. Jennings.

677
00:30:13.538 --> 00:30:16.361
your son may have been
intentionally infected.

678
00:30:16.470 --> 00:30:18.149
Is this because...

679
00:30:18.243 --> 00:30:20.129
Is this because...?

680
00:30:20.497 --> 00:30:21.580
If Connor was targeted

681
00:30:21.668 --> 00:30:24.656
by someone capable
of this kind of attack.

682
00:30:24.973 --> 00:30:27.580
it has to be connected
to his father.

683
00:30:27.650 --> 00:30:29.334
His father?

684
00:30:30.832 --> 00:30:33.520
When I was a young staffer
on the Hill.

685
00:30:34.092 --> 00:30:36.748
I had an affair with the man
I was working for.

686
00:30:36.831 --> 00:30:41.316
We were stupid. and...
I got pregnant.

687
00:30:42.896 --> 00:30:46.962
Even then. he had his eyes
set on a big political future.

688
00:30:47.057 --> 00:30:49.504
so I agreed to go away.

689
00:30:49.599 --> 00:30:54.587
I made a deal to receive
ongoing support from him.

690
00:30:56.270 --> 00:30:58.610
Senator Hawkins--
he's the target.

691
00:30:58.753 --> 00:30:59.998
The tested the virus
on his son.

692
00:31:00.090 --> 00:31:02.022
the closest
possible genetic match.

693
00:31:02.118 --> 00:31:04.977
You need to find the Senator
before Karakurt does.

694
00:31:39.733 --> 00:31:41.111
Hey. Keen!

695
00:31:41.818 --> 00:31:43.461
Samar's reaching out
to Hawkins' office.

696
00:31:43.551 --> 00:31:44.231
He's not inside.

697
00:31:44.323 --> 00:31:46.155
so we still got a shot
of keeping him clear.

698
00:31:47.325 --> 00:31:49.973
I'll check the drive-ups.
Any word from Metro?

699
00:31:50.052 --> 00:31:52.747
Negative. If Karakurt's inside.
nobody's spotted him yet.

700
00:31:52.832 --> 00:31:54.645
Step up. please.
Name?

701
00:31:54.937 --> 00:31:57.516
Flemming. European Wire.

702
00:32:04.252 --> 00:32:06.856
Flemming. press badge 6362.

703
00:32:07.892 --> 00:32:09.176
We're gonna need
to check the case.

704
00:32:18.481 --> 00:32:20.050
We're good.

705
00:32:21.077 --> 00:32:23.226
He's on the Main Justice
press list.

706
00:32:24.426 --> 00:32:26.594
It's time. Harold.
Call Tom Connolly.

707
00:32:26.701 --> 00:32:28.643
Tell him you need to
see him immediately.

708
00:32:28.762 --> 00:32:30.481
I'm assuming at the moment
he has no idea

709
00:32:30.588 --> 00:32:33.019
you've identified
Karakurt's intended victim.

710
00:32:33.161 --> 00:32:35.014
which is why
you need to tell him.

711
00:32:35.114 --> 00:32:36.096
Why would I do that?

712
00:32:36.180 --> 00:32:37.664
Because he'll be
caught off guard.

713
00:32:37.747 --> 00:32:40.185
And in addition to enhancing
your credibility with him.

714
00:32:40.306 --> 00:32:42.501
it'll make him doubt
whether or not to move forward.

715
00:32:42.592 --> 00:32:43.914
You think
he'll call off the attack?

716
00:32:44.006 --> 00:32:45.093
I think it's worth the attempt.

717
00:32:45.174 --> 00:32:46.774
What's the latest
from Agents Keen and Ressler?

718
00:32:46.866 --> 00:32:48.445
Still no sign of Karakurt.

719
00:32:48.527 --> 00:32:51.216
Agent Navabi's on the line now
with one of Hawkins' aides.

720
00:32:51.629 --> 00:32:53.677
Listen to me.
It's not a<i> potential</i> threat.

721
00:32:53.769 --> 00:32:54.647
The Bureau has confirmed

722
00:32:54.769 --> 00:32:57.516
that a direct attack
on the Senator is imminent.

723
00:32:57.940 --> 00:33:00.662
No. I cannot confirm my source.

724
00:33:01.796 --> 00:33:03.252
Then you need to find
whoever<i> is</i> with him

725
00:33:03.349 --> 00:33:04.387
and deliver the message.

726
00:33:04.472 --> 00:33:06.007
It's not safe
to attend the service.

727
00:33:06.085 --> 00:33:07.226
You need to find him.

728
00:33:07.309 --> 00:33:08.678
You'll be third to the podium.
Senator.

729
00:33:08.782 --> 00:33:10.519
After the minister
and the family representative.

730
00:33:10.611 --> 00:33:11.838
they'll have a moment
of silence. and then--

731
00:33:11.927 --> 00:33:12.834
We'll be sitting here forever.

732
00:33:12.923 --> 00:33:15.058
This is fine. Patrick.
I'll walk.

733
00:33:18.804 --> 00:33:20.317
Senator Hawkins. how are you?

734
00:33:21.285 --> 00:33:23.600
- Welcome. sir.
- Thank you.

735
00:33:41.646 --> 00:33:43.934
Harold. your cooperation
was instrumental

736
00:33:44.033 --> 00:33:45.265
in Karakurt's escape.

737
00:33:45.353 --> 00:33:47.358
Everything's on track.
thanks to you.

738
00:33:47.445 --> 00:33:48.392
Don't thank me yet.

739
00:33:48.480 --> 00:33:49.480
Why?
Is there a problem?

740
00:33:49.603 --> 00:33:51.371
My people are closing in
on him now.

741
00:33:51.463 --> 00:33:53.095
They know the Orea bombing
was just the first

742
00:33:53.187 --> 00:33:54.216
in a series of attacks.

743
00:33:54.302 --> 00:33:56.081
They know about the virus.

744
00:33:56.190 --> 00:33:57.374
I see.

745
00:33:59.434 --> 00:34:01.642
Well. thank you
for letting me know.

746
00:34:02.898 --> 00:34:04.307
But<i> why</i> are you
letting me know?

747
00:34:04.394 --> 00:34:05.906
And don't tell me
you want to help

748
00:34:05.990 --> 00:34:07.216
because I know
you'd like nothing better

749
00:34:07.295 --> 00:34:08.769
than to strangle me right now.

750
00:34:08.860 --> 00:34:10.780
You're right.
I'm letting you know

751
00:34:10.877 --> 00:34:12.422
because I want you
to call it off.

752
00:34:12.509 --> 00:34:13.823
I can't control Reddington.
and I can't

753
00:34:13.918 --> 00:34:17.418
misdirect my people again
without drawing suspicion.

754
00:34:17.705 --> 00:34:20.376
It's only a matter of time
until they stop Karakurt.

755
00:34:20.462 --> 00:34:21.791
Stop him from what?

756
00:34:21.898 --> 00:34:23.768
They don't even know
his target.

757
00:34:25.279 --> 00:34:27.247
Clifford Hawkins.

758
00:34:28.133 --> 00:34:29.654
Call it off. Tom.

759
00:34:29.756 --> 00:34:30.824
If the Director
really wants him dead.

760
00:34:30.915 --> 00:34:33.336
he can find another way
on another day.

761
00:34:33.709 --> 00:34:36.714
No.
Today is the day.

762
00:34:36.799 --> 00:34:41.138
I appreciate your concern.
but everything should be fine.

763
00:34:46.805 --> 00:34:49.656
Strange days. don't you think?

764
00:34:49.741 --> 00:34:53.330
Assassins don't need knives
or guns or bombs.

765
00:34:53.424 --> 00:34:55.472
All you have to do
is answer a few questions

766
00:34:55.574 --> 00:34:57.937
and shake the wrong man's hand.

767
00:35:01.096 --> 00:35:03.238
The press corps.
Get over there now.

768
00:35:03.402 --> 00:35:05.474
I think Karakurt
may be posing as a reporter.

769
00:35:05.571 --> 00:35:07.486
Hey. he's just pulling
into the service now.

770
00:35:16.079 --> 00:35:17.580
Senator Hawkins.

771
00:35:32.245 --> 00:35:33.325
Get him away!
Get him away from us!

772
00:35:33.412 --> 00:35:35.145
Come with us. sir!

773
00:35:43.229 --> 00:35:44.095
What the hell's going on?

774
00:35:44.198 --> 00:35:45.894
The man responsible
for the Orea bombing--

775
00:35:45.987 --> 00:35:47.742
Karakurt? I was briefed.
Was that him?

776
00:35:47.833 --> 00:35:48.914
We'll explain everything. sir.

777
00:35:48.996 --> 00:35:50.680
Right now. we need to get you
to a secure location.

778
00:35:50.782 --> 00:35:51.779
Thank you.

779
00:35:51.909 --> 00:35:55.391
Please. call my wife.
tell her I'm okay?

780
00:35:56.305 --> 00:35:58.796
Sir?

781
00:35:58.880 --> 00:36:00.087
Sir!

782
00:36:00.175 --> 00:36:01.446
We need to get him
to a hospital now!

783
00:36:01.528 --> 00:36:02.748
He's been infected!

784
00:36:06.429 --> 00:36:08.002
Sir!

785
00:36:11.925 --> 00:36:13.704
Bethesda says
Hawkins is critical.

786
00:36:13.805 --> 00:36:15.396
They've called in
the hospital chaplain.

787
00:36:16.146 --> 00:36:17.689
He didn't touch Karakurt?

788
00:36:17.785 --> 00:36:19.141
No. sir.

789
00:36:19.535 --> 00:36:20.694
Then what the hell happened?

790
00:36:20.788 --> 00:36:22.115
Karakurt's in holding.

791
00:36:22.221 --> 00:36:24.119
We're gonna take a run at him
and find out.

792
00:36:24.277 --> 00:36:25.450
Best I could tell.

793
00:36:25.655 --> 00:36:28.356
Hawkins just melted down
next to Keen.

794
00:36:48.129 --> 00:36:49.834
Karakurt.

795
00:36:49.981 --> 00:36:51.621
That means "Spider." right?

796
00:36:51.723 --> 00:36:53.887
Kara-what?

797
00:36:53.981 --> 00:36:55.715
Huh? Look. I don't know
what that is.

798
00:36:55.812 --> 00:36:57.119
My name is Jonas Flemming.

799
00:36:57.206 --> 00:36:58.828
I'm a reporter
for the European Wire.

800
00:36:58.915 --> 00:37:00.512
I live in Rotterdam.

801
00:37:00.997 --> 00:37:02.630
We're gonna try this again.

802
00:37:03.007 --> 00:37:04.290
We know who you are.

803
00:37:04.395 --> 00:37:06.909
That's you outside the Orea.

804
00:37:07.194 --> 00:37:08.891
You exited a rental truck
less than a minute

805
00:37:08.981 --> 00:37:10.925
before it exploded
and destroyed the building.

806
00:37:11.009 --> 00:37:13.281
We have a recording
of you and Andropov.

807
00:37:13.368 --> 00:37:16.037
We know he engineered a drug
designed to kill the Senator.

808
00:37:16.134 --> 00:37:17.420
We know you're infected.

809
00:37:17.517 --> 00:37:18.636
No. no. no. no.

810
00:37:18.743 --> 00:37:21.137
My credentials were taken
from me when I arrived.

811
00:37:21.270 --> 00:37:23.893
but they were vetted
by your Department Of Justice.

812
00:37:23.996 --> 00:37:24.670
Please. call.

813
00:37:24.761 --> 00:37:26.152
You didn't touch the Senator.

814
00:37:26.314 --> 00:37:28.468
How was the virus delivered?

815
00:37:31.153 --> 00:37:32.269
You can rig your little story.

816
00:37:32.368 --> 00:37:34.438
but you can't rig your blood.

817
00:37:34.523 --> 00:37:35.895
We're running it right now.

818
00:37:36.009 --> 00:37:37.256
And when it comes back positive

819
00:37:37.344 --> 00:37:41.767
for that virus that
killed Hawkins. we got you.

820
00:37:49.198 --> 00:37:50.820
Hello. Anton.

821
00:37:51.059 --> 00:37:52.095
Relax.

822
00:37:52.229 --> 00:37:54.198
If I had bad intentions
for this visit.

823
00:37:54.289 --> 00:37:55.753
you'd know by now.

824
00:37:56.227 --> 00:37:58.153
You're Raymond Reddington.

825
00:37:58.242 --> 00:37:58.937
I am.

826
00:37:59.040 --> 00:38:01.518
And if I'm right.
you're the same Anton Velov

827
00:38:01.626 --> 00:38:05.075
who once led
a Spetsnaz Special Forces Unit

828
00:38:05.249 --> 00:38:07.421
called The Zarubin Group.

829
00:38:07.545 --> 00:38:09.889
I'm surprised we never met.

830
00:38:09.980 --> 00:38:11.283
For many years.

831
00:38:11.380 --> 00:38:14.903
while you were still
with US Counterintelligence.

832
00:38:15.075 --> 00:38:19.154
I considered you
the KGB's greatest enemy.

833
00:38:19.253 --> 00:38:21.384
Oh. my God.

834
00:38:22.240 --> 00:38:25.049
That feels like ages ago.

835
00:38:25.698 --> 00:38:28.258
For what it's worth.
I was young.

836
00:38:28.407 --> 00:38:33.509
I had no concept of what
a real enemy looked like.

837
00:38:34.059 --> 00:38:36.230
But I do know.

838
00:38:36.894 --> 00:38:38.113
Which is why I'm hoping

839
00:38:38.221 --> 00:38:41.356
you and I might prove
to be fast friends.

840
00:38:42.020 --> 00:38:43.871
What can I do?

841
00:38:44.031 --> 00:38:46.919
I know you're working
with the CIA as an informant

842
00:38:47.002 --> 00:38:49.876
for the Office of Russian
and European Analysis.

843
00:38:49.977 --> 00:38:52.384
Since those agents are
tragically no longer with us.

844
00:38:52.473 --> 00:38:55.796
I was thinking perhaps you might
become an asset for<i> me.</i>

845
00:38:56.228 --> 00:38:57.550
The American government.

846
00:38:57.638 --> 00:38:59.700
They may not
be done with me yet.

847
00:38:59.930 --> 00:39:02.514
I got a phone call from FBI.

848
00:39:02.619 --> 00:39:05.833
An agent named Elizabeth Keen.

849
00:39:05.921 --> 00:39:08.235
Really? What about?

850
00:39:08.342 --> 00:39:09.873
She wants to meet.

851
00:39:09.965 --> 00:39:13.786
She was asking
about Katarina Rostova.

852
00:39:13.876 --> 00:39:15.725
Did you know Katarina Rostova?

853
00:39:15.814 --> 00:39:17.761
No. not personally.

854
00:39:17.851 --> 00:39:22.527
All I know are the same
old ghost stories we all share.

855
00:39:22.638 --> 00:39:25.889
Well. if you were in my employ.
I would have to insist

856
00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:28.357
you not speak to anyone
from the FBI

857
00:39:28.464 --> 00:39:31.545
or any other
US intelligence agency.

858
00:39:31.637 --> 00:39:33.535
Of course.

859
00:39:33.787 --> 00:39:37.310
And Agent Keen.
she wasn't the first.

860
00:39:37.439 --> 00:39:41.150
Sometime back. two men
from Justice Department

861
00:39:41.254 --> 00:39:43.409
come and ask me about Katarina.

862
00:39:43.550 --> 00:39:45.854
I suppose they think
I am one of the few people left

863
00:39:45.985 --> 00:39:49.470
who still remember
the old stories.

864
00:39:50.834 --> 00:39:52.520
What sort of stories?

865
00:39:53.026 --> 00:39:56.449
They were asking
about her KGB contacts.

866
00:39:56.558 --> 00:40:01.226
where she lived.
and about a child.

867
00:40:03.284 --> 00:40:04.916
They asked about a child?

868
00:40:05.005 --> 00:40:07.186
Yes. many times.

869
00:40:07.274 --> 00:40:09.704
"Tell me
about her child."

870
00:40:09.803 --> 00:40:13.538
I said. "All I know
is they say she had a daughter."

871
00:40:13.630 --> 00:40:14.991
Dembe. the phone.

872
00:40:15.128 --> 00:40:16.978
How many times
are we gonna go through this?

873
00:40:17.078 --> 00:40:19.582
That picture isn't me.
Call my office.

874
00:40:19.675 --> 00:40:21.252
Check my visa.
check my identity.

875
00:40:21.334 --> 00:40:22.934
We know you're working
for the Cabal.

876
00:40:23.054 --> 00:40:24.010
We know
what they're capable of.

877
00:40:24.098 --> 00:40:25.396
Was this the plan all along.

878
00:40:25.485 --> 00:40:27.021
to protect you
with this identity?

879
00:40:27.113 --> 00:40:29.260
The Cabal has people in the
government all over the world.

880
00:40:29.347 --> 00:40:31.834
It wouldn't be hard for them
to create a Jonas Flemming.

881
00:40:32.025 --> 00:40:33.817
give him a history...

882
00:40:39.562 --> 00:40:40.731
The Crime Lab just called.

883
00:40:40.824 --> 00:40:43.393
They're saying his blood
tested negative for the virus.

884
00:40:43.491 --> 00:40:46.692
Negative?
That's not possible.

885
00:40:50.785 --> 00:40:52.184
Hey. I got to
call you right back.

886
00:40:52.269 --> 00:40:53.869
Lizzy. you need
to get out of there now.

887
00:40:53.962 --> 00:40:55.668
Why? Where are you?
What's going on?

888
00:40:55.758 --> 00:40:56.799
You've been set up.

889
00:40:56.901 --> 00:40:58.578
The Cabal's been asking
about you. Lizzy.

890
00:40:58.676 --> 00:41:01.117
They know who your mother was.
You've been set up.

891
00:41:01.223 --> 00:41:03.302
You were there when
the Orea building was bombed.

892
00:41:03.379 --> 00:41:05.297
They wanted you
to save Clifford Hawkins.

893
00:41:05.384 --> 00:41:07.039
They sent
Karakurt to the memorial

894
00:41:07.165 --> 00:41:09.005
to make you think
he was the threat

895
00:41:09.092 --> 00:41:12.051
so you would secure the Senator
and infect him in the process.

896
00:41:12.140 --> 00:41:13.414
I don't have the virus.

897
00:41:13.495 --> 00:41:14.991
You<i> do.</i> Lizzy.

898
00:41:15.128 --> 00:41:17.106
I don't need a test
to know that you do.

899
00:41:17.210 --> 00:41:18.745
Your mother was a Russian spy.

900
00:41:18.846 --> 00:41:20.763
and now they've made it
look like you are. too.

901
00:41:20.841 --> 00:41:22.160
You have the virus.

902
00:41:22.231 --> 00:41:25.754
You infected the Senator.
and now they will come for you.

903
00:41:25.843 --> 00:41:28.249
You need
to get out of there now.

904
00:41:43.593 --> 00:41:50.128
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

